# T1059.001 - Command and Scripting Interpreter: PowerShell

**MITRE ATT&CK Technique:** [T1059.001](https://attack.mitre.org/techniques/T1059/001/)

**Tactic:** Execution

**Objective:** Execute malicious or test PowerShell scripts on Windows 10 to simulate real-world attacker use of PowerShell for payload execution and living-off-the-land.

## Attack Attempts Summary

### 1. Attempt from Kali Linux (Remote Execution)
**Tools tried:**
- Impacket (`wmiexec.py`, `psexec.py`)
- Custom `.ps1` payload delivery via SCP + SSH
- Linux launcher scripts (`run-edge.sh`, `quick-edge.sh`)

**Issues Encountered:**
- Remote execution failed or was unreliable
- Some payloads did not run properly on the target

**Troubleshooting Done:**
- Tried different Impacket modules and command formats
- Used `-ExecutionPolicy Bypass`
- Created and transferred custom PowerShell payloads (e.g. open Edge → google.com → close browser)

**Result:** Remote PowerShell execution via Impacket was inconsistent in this lab environment.

### 2. Successful Method: Atomic Red Team (Local Execution)

**Command Used:**
```powershell
# Run all tests for T1059.001
Invoke-AtomicTest T1059.001

# Specific useful tests
Invoke-AtomicTest T1059.001 -TestNumbers 1
Invoke-AtomicTest T1059.001 -TestNumbers 10   # Fileless execution example
